\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{eqnarray*}
\frac{\text{d}^{2}V}{\text{d}x^{2}} & \neq & k\\
F(x) & = & -k(x-x_{0})\\
F & \propto & -\text{displacement}\\
 & = & \text{resulting force}
\end{eqnarray*}

\end_inset

So small displacement from the equilibrium will give oscillations about
 the equilibrium,
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
F=m\ddot{x}=-kx
\]

\end_inset

This is the simple harmonic oscillator.
 So it there is a sufficiently small displacement if any system from the
 equilibrium, that will produce SHM.
\end_layout

