\begin_layout Section
Damping
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
In reality, dissipative forces are usually present.
 These will convert the energy of motion of this oscillator into other forms.
 And so the oscillations will decay.
 The simplest type is one that is proportional to velocity,
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
F=-b\ddot{x}
\]

\end_inset

Then the equation of motion becomes
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
m\ddot{x}+b\dot{x}+kx=0
\]

\end_inset


\bar under
\noun on
