 This can be written as 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\frac{(x-a\epsilon)^{2}}{a^{2}}+\frac{y^{2}}{b^{2}}=1\qquad\text{Elliptical orbit}
\]

\end_inset

where 
\begin_inset Formula $a=\frac{r_{0}}{1-\epsilon^{2}}=-\frac{k}{2E}$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $b^{2}=r_{0}a=-\frac{l^{2}}{2mE}$
\end_inset

.
